  "response": "Cotton fibers have been used for thousands of years, with evidence of cotton cultivation and use dating back to around 5,000 BCE in the Indus Valley region, which is present-day Pakistan and northwest India. Archaeological findings indicate that cotton textiles were being produced and used during this period. Additionally, traces of cotton have been found in ancient Egyptian tombs dating back to around 3,000 BCE, highlighting the long history of cotton as a textile material in various cultures.",
